[
  {
    "path": "infra/compose/observability.yml",
    "line": 94,
    "severity": "high",
    "message": "New `redis-exporter` service exposes Redis metrics on :9121, but `infra/observability/prometheus/prometheus.yml` has no scrape_config targeting `redis-exporter:9121` (it only scrapes prometheus, otel-collector, and postgres-exporter). The exporter is added to the prod-bound `observability.yml` overlay, so Redis — a prod runtime data store defined in `base.yml:40` — produces zero collected metrics. An exporter with no scrape job is dead weight: the observability never actually reaches Prometheus.",
    "suggestion": "Add a scrape job to `prometheus.yml`:\n  - job_name: redis\n    static_configs:\n      - targets: [\"redis-exporter:9121\"]"
  },
  {
    "path": "infra/compose/observability.yml",
    "line": 94,
    "severity": "medium",
    "message": "The new `redis-exporter` wires up a Redis observability surface, but there is no corresponding alert rule file under `infra/observability/prometheus/alerts/` (existing files cover only alertmanager, otel-collector, postgres, prometheus, slo). Redis is a prod runtime dependency, so adding the exporter without any alerts (e.g. redis down, memory/maxmemory pressure, rejected connections, replication lag) leaves the surface unmonitored despite now being instrumented.",
    "suggestion": "Add `infra/observability/prometheus/alerts/redis_alerts.yml` with at least a RedisDown alert (`redis_up == 0`) routed to an existing Alertmanager receiver, plus memory/eviction alerts."
  },
  {
    "path": "infra/compose/observability.yml",
    "line": 94,
    "severity": "medium",
    "message": "No Grafana dashboard accompanies the new `redis-exporter`. Existing dashboards in `infra/observability/grafana/dashboards/` cover otel-collector, postgres, prometheus, and slo — there is no redis.json. The pattern in this repo is exporter + scrape job + alert rule + dashboard per surface (cf. postgres-exporter, which has postgres_alerts.yml and postgres.json); the Redis surface is missing the dashboard half of that contract.",
    "suggestion": "Add `infra/observability/grafana/dashboards/redis.json` with panels for the key `redis_exporter` metrics (uptime, memory, connected clients, ops/sec, evictions) so the new metrics are visualized, mirroring the postgres dashboard."
  }
]
